76561197965604084,Recommended,501110,29098845,Posted: 7 January,all,Brother Skaldir,"FIrst up, a bit of a warning.  This one has a learning curve to it, especially if you're using the Vive controllers.  Expect to spend your first thirty minutes or so smashing into cliffs and trying to make sense of what the hell is going on.  The controls need a very subtle touch, and figuring out exactly how to hold them is a bit of a trial-and-error process right now.Do NOT give up.  Once it ""clicks"" it is amazing.  I have no idea what ""real"" wingsuit flying is like, but this feels spectacular.  I found myself frequently holding my breath during close-shave passes with cliffsides and narrow gaps.  Going from my first fumbling attempts at flight to screaming through concrete pipes at high speed without fear feels amazing.  I've only explored the first two drop sites, and I'm already hooked."
