,Recommended,501110,29612450,Posted: 31 January,all,Meatcicle,"Playing with HTC Vive:1. This is the game you are looking for.2. Do not rage quit and ask for a refund, that just means that you a) haven't logged enough time with the Vive and/or b) you haven't spent enough time getting a feel for this game -- practice more before you miss out on this game!!!3. Bravo to the devs for making the controls so intuitive -- once you get it, you will get it. Like those wierd ""3D"" posters from (ahem) 25 years ago...4. For Noobs -- I have found that sitting in my chair, resting my elbows on my knees as a starting position works well, and use your wrists for most motion. It is about feel, and VERY important to look ahead (like a race car driver looks ahead into the furthest turn they can see, your body will react intuitively as long as you LOOK where you WANT to go. More practice!5. It really is awesome!Looking forward to more content, better graphics (as time progresses), and multiplayer COOP would be the cat's meow. MEOW!Cheers!"
