,Recommended,501110,34510264,Posted: 26 August,all,FastLawyer,"Played on Oculus Rift with Touch.  Honestly, this is a fun and challenging game.  And there's a surprising amount of content here, believe it or not.  There's several drop points, each with different paths, which means there's many jumps/vistas to do and scores to chase.  Granted, I haven't been able to get past the second drop point after playing for 30 minutes.The main things I don't like about this game are the controls and the lack of a good tutorial.  Also, the difficulty spike is quite large between the first drop zone and the second drop zone.  The graphics are good, but not great.  And for whatever reason, I didn' feel fully immersed when flying.I think part of the reason is because you have to look down or up to control your flight up and down horizontally, meanwhile you're standing up vertically (you can also do seated, but bleh on that).  Also you neck will start feeling some strain after a while with the current setup.  Why couldn't gliding up or down have been controlled using the motion controllers?  Easy solution is to make a slight twist of the wrists for up or down (like an eagle would use it wings or plane using its flaps).  That way you can look around wherever you want free from the motion.  You're already using your arms to control side movements.Still, I enjoyed playing this game.  I think it's fun if you can ignore the above issues.  Just wish the above issues were fixed so that more time could be spent enjoying the game versus being frustrated.  Also it would be nice if there was a relaxed, ""guided"" option, meaning much easier jumps to just enjoy the views and feeling of flight with no score.Rating 7/10"
